  \label{fig:pdf}}
\end{figure}


Figure~\ref{fig:pdf_ratio} shows the PDF ratios ($PDF^{bkgd}/PDF^{sig}$) for $\Delta$ToF, $\Delta y \times q$, $\Delta z$, and $n\sigma_{\pi}$, respectively. 
A linear extrapolation (solid red line) is used to obtain the ratios between points in the middle region while a linear fit (dashed red line) is used for the side regions.
In this method, only three variables, $\Delta y\times q$, $\Delta z$ and $n\sigma_{\pi}$, are used to calculate the $R$ value for the probed muon. 
The cut values on $\Delta$ToF is fixed from the N-1 iteration method due to the mismatch of signal PDF between data and simulation.
Figure~\ref{fig:LHratio_muid} shows the discriminating power of the Likelihood Ratio method, and the cut value on $R$ variable, $R > 0.05$, is chosen to maximize the significance of the $J/\psi$ signal.

