\section{Conclusion}
\label{concl}

The MTD is a newly installed detector dedicated to study muons in STAR with low kinematic cutoff.

In this paper, we demonstrated three different methods on muon identification, i.e. straight cut, N-1 iteration and Likelihood Ratio method, each of which can reduce the background level above 70\% and keep the $J/\psi$ signals with about 60\% of efficiency. 

With this muon identification capability, the MTD provides a good opportunity to study heavy-ion physics with muons, especially the quarkonium states, in the STAR experiment. 



